Using Run Options to Invoke Methods

The abstraction framework allows you to call multiple methods in sequence by specifying a run option. Various run options are provided to cater to the most common sequences.

For example, by specifying a single run option, you can call either the GetData, MatchData, and SetAttributes methods sequentially, or the GetData, MatchData, and AddProducts methods sequentially.

You can also use run option zero to warm up the abstraction service.

While it is possible to use the abstraction service methods and patterns atomically, without using any of the run options, it's recommended that you use the run options to ensure a smoother flow and optimized performance.

The following table provides a list of run options used in Multiplay Subscription Management along with the corresponding methods and patterns invoked by each run option:

Run Option 0
Run Option 0 invokes the WarmUpService operation. You can use this run option to load the abstraction framework into runtime cache, before making any other call to the abstraction framework. Using this run option improves performance by increasing the probability of having the abstraction service cached when the first real call to the service is made. When you call the abstraction framework with Run Option 0, ensure that it is called in asynchronous mode, so that the workflow progresses without waiting for this operation to complete.
Run Option 1
Run Option 1 invokes the GetData method. This method uses the integration key or workflow name as input and fetches the custom metadata of the corresponding targets.
Run Option 2
Run Option 2 invokes the GetData and the MatchData methods. After getting data using GetData, the MatchData method matches the attributes of the target with values received from the workflow.
Run Option 3
Run Option 3 updates items in the cart based on input received from a workflow. This run option invokes the GetData, MatchData, and PostData methods. The GetData and MatchData methods perform the same actions as in Run Option 1 and Run Option 2. Run Option 3 additionally invokes the SetAttributes pattern of the PostData method. It updates attributes of line items in the cart. Internally, SetAttributes calls the putCartsItem API.
Run Option 4
Run Option 4 removes an item from the cart. This run option invokes the GetData, MatchData, and PostData methods. The GetData and MatchData methods perform the same actions as in Run Option 1 and Run Option 2. Run Option 4 additionally invokes the DisconnectProduct pattern of the PostData method to remove the specified product from the cart.
Run Option 5
Run Option 5 adds a product to the cart. This run option invokes the GetData, MatchData, and PostData methods. The GetData and MatchData methods perform the same actions as in Run Option 1 and Run Option 2. Run Option 5 additionally invokes the AddProduct pattern of the PostData method to add the specified product to the cart.
Run Option 6
Run Option 6 replaces a product in a cart. This run option invokes the GetData, MatchData, and PostData methods. The GetData and MatchData methods perform the same actions as in Run Option 1 and Run Option 2. Run Option 6 additionally invokes first the DisconnectProduct pattern and then the AddProduct pattern of the PostData method to replace the specified product in the cart.
Run Option 7
Run Option 7 replaces a product in the cart and sets attributes for that product. This run option invokes the GetData, MatchData, and PostData methods. The GetData and MatchData methods perform the same actions as in Run Option 1 and Run Option 2. Run Option 7 additionally invokes the DisconnectProduct, AddProduct, and SetAttribute patterns of the PostData method to replace the specified product in the cart and set attributes.
Run Option 8
Run Option 8 adds a product to the cart and sets attributes. This run option invokes the GetData, MatchData, and PostData methods. The GetData and MatchData methods perform the same actions as in Run Option 1 and Run Option 2. Run Option 8 additionally invokes the AddProduct and SetAttribute patterns of the PostData method to add the specified product in the cart and set attributes.
Run Option 11
Run Option 11 updates one or more attributes on one or more line items directly in the database without using Vlocity Standard APIs. This run option invokes the GetData, MatchData, and SetAttributesTECH methods. The GetData and MatchData methods perform the same actions as in Run Option 1 and Run Option 2. Run Option 11 additionally updates attributes on the specified line items.
Run Option 12
Run Option 12 updates one or more fields or attributes on one or more line items directly in the database without using Vlocity Standard APIs. This run option invokes the GetData, MatchData, SetAttributesTECH, and SetFieldTECH methods. The GetData and MatchData methods perform the same actions as in Run Option 1 and Run Option 2. Run Option 12 additionally updates fields and attributes on the specified line items.
Run Option 16
Run Option 16 fetches attributes and fields for one or more line items in one or more carts. This run option invokes the GetData, MatchData, GetAttributes, and GetFields methods. The GetData and MatchData methods perform the same actions as in Run Option 1 and Run Option 2. Run Option 16 additionally gets information about fields and attributes of the specified targets.
